        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 5:56PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 556 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hayden, or 6 miles northwest of Amistad, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hayden.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
